messages.content: “Ha ha, what?”
Who’s this asshole?
“Hello, Frank.”

"Hello, dear Baron. I believe I've made myself clear. Push him forward, now." Frank.

"That man's the boss of the Hellhound's assassins! He's obviously going to kill me!" Washington struggles in vain.
Nash raises an eyebrow. “Oh, I’m sorry, is the terrorist begging for his life now?”

"I'm not a terrorist you moron!" Washington.

The archer aims his bow at Frank.

"Let me be clear here. I *can* kill all of you if I need to. I just make it a policy not to kill people I'm not paid for as much as I can. Otherwise I'd have no money and this city would have no people." Frank.
“You are definitely a terrorist.”

"This isn't the time to fight. We aren't going to let you kill my father." Aliza brandishes her rapier threateningly.

"What do we do?" The archer whispers to Nash.

“He wants a trade, doesn’t he?” Nash bites his lower lip. “I’m not one to negotiate with terrorists, but if it’s between a man who’s done nothing and a man who tried to betray the Empire, that’s, well…”

"Alright." He lowers his bow.

"What are you doing?" Aliza.
“Do you have a better idea, genius?” He snaps at her.

"Not killing my father!?" Aliza.

"Tch. You're as spineless as I thought, Dorrance." Washington. 

"Just shove him forward now, okay?" Frank.
“Stop calling me fucking Dorrance!”
“My name is EDWARDSON! Nash! Edwardson! I’m a member of the Edwardson family! A beloved member!”
"You shouldn't even be counted as a fucking Soltarian!" Washington shouts in anger.
“Yet who is Edward?” I contribute to the conversation. “I hardly think this quarreling about lineage is to your benefit, Washington.”
"Edward was a prince a really long time ago. It doesn't matter now." Aliza.
Nash grips his head. “I was raised here! I live here! I’ll kill and die for this country! I’m a Soltarian! Eat shit, you fffuckin’..”

The archer kicks Washington forward, knocking into the reach of Frank.

"You soulless sons of bitches!" Washington grits his teeth as he lands next to Frank.

"Oh, I'm sorry... Did you think I was going to kill him? Of course not! The Queen just has more work for him." Frank grabs Washington's arm.

"So the great and mighty leader of the faceless is just another pawn of the queen? Don't you have any pride?" Washington.

"Please, Mr Hamill. You cannot provoke me. I'm not so foolish as to be opposed to helping my allies once in a while. I don't consider that a matter of pride." Frank.
Nash doesn’t say anything. He’s still kind of coping and seething.
“There is a rather straightforward decision; either we attempt to fight, possibly succeeding and possibly all dying, or we let these two leave. I’m opting for the latter.”

"Even you, Ally?" Aliza.

"Glad you could mostly all be reasonable. Be seeing you!" Frank suddenly vanishes, along with Washington and Theodoric.

"Why’d he take the kid too!?" Archer.
“Hey!!!” Nash yells at the empty space where Frank just was. “Come back! That wasn’t the agreement!”
“What?” I squint. “That isn’t good.”

"Well… We don’t know where he went." Archer.

"Dad!" Aliza runs out of the room calling out for her father repeatedly.
“Urghhh.” Nash scowls, slapping his forehead. “This is such a clusterfuck.”

“Washington should be fine.” I mutter reassuringly before realizing Aliza’s left. “They’re nominally allies, even if he doesn’t seem too pleased with that. But taking Theo? Was it insurance, so we don’t try to pursue? That seems counterproductive.”
"We don’t care, dude." Archer.

Nash just sort of… slumps over. With Washington gone, all the hatred and spite and panic that’s been driving him has disappeared, leaving behind only a bone-deep exhaustion. He presses his hands harder against his eyes, blocking out the light, until his vision becomes nothing but fragmented and fuzzy patches. He makes another vaguely upset noise.
“Okay.” I leave the room and pursue my companion.
Aliza runs out of the building.
I follow.
She keeps calling out to her dad, receiving no response.
Unfortunate. I think about saying something but don’t. I’ll be here when I’m needed.
"Where are you!?"
“We’d need to track down their base of operations…”
"But... How?"
“I…” I sigh. “I don’t know.”
"I've been there... Maybe if I focus, I can figure out some clues."
“It’s possible.”
"Uh… There weren’t any windows. So maybe it was underground or something?"
“That would make sense. I think most legitimate establishments on the surface are accounted for on the city’s floor plan.”
"That’s a good idea actually. Do you think we could get our hands on that?"
“I can probably arrange that.”
Your likeliest contact to have this is probably Maxwell Skylar.
Then off I go.
She follows. Are you headed to the guild hall or his home?
The former, I guess.
The guild hall is currently under reconstruction. Doesn’t seem like Maxwell is around.
Dang. "The latter, I guess." I say this out loud incoherently.
"What?"
"I'm looking for Maxwell Skylar, but it's doubtful he's here."
"Oh, the merchant?"
"Yyyyes."
"Where would he be then?"
"Maybe at his own private dwelling."
"Do you know where that is?"
"Yyes." I nod. Then head there.
"Well, you saved your mom at least."
“Ah.. yeah.” Nash says emptily. Then he shoots upright. “But Kori and Oswalda.. they’re fine, r-right?” *Why are you asking Orion? It’s not like he would know.*
"Yeah, they’re just in Kori’s room probably. I don’t see why that Frank guy would’ve attacked them."
((going to eat lunch rq I’ll brb))
((ok back))
“I.. want to check on them.”
"Uh… Okay. I’ll be waiting here with Ruth. Don’t take too long, okay?"
"Yeah."
Nash leaves for Kori's room.
Oswalda is standing over Kori, watching her as she sleeps. "Hello, Nash. She’s resting, so please be quiet."
"Alright." Nash says quietly. "Is everything.. everything's okay with you both, right?"
"Well, it will be soon." Oswalda.
"What do you mean?"
"Kori needs a long rest to heal."
"Yeah.. yeah, that makes sense."
Nash pauses.
"Are.. *you* okay? M. Mom."

She smiles. "Yes I am, Nash. I used to fight at the old arena when I was your age. Have you ever been there?" You definitely haven’t. This is your first time hearing there was ever even an arena in the city. The concept is so barbarian, after all.
Nash flinches. "A-an arena? Isn't that, somewhat..."
He trails off.

"Oh you’re right, they shut it down before you came here, didn’t they…?" Oswalda reminisces with a smile. "The emperor decided it was too violent to encourage blood sport here so these days people go to other Soltarian cities for that sort of thing. Mostly, he just wanted more soldiers I think. He just had a convenient excuse for it when those kobolds attacked back then." She cuts herself off. "I’m sorry, you probably don’t care for the history lesson, do you? It doesn’t concern you. All you need to know is that the duchess saved me from what the others had to go through."
"The history of this country does concern me!" He snaps, before immediately tempering himself. "Sorry. It's good that she saved you." He smiles. "She's always been kind that way."

"If you’re interested, I can explain a bit more, I’m sorry. The men were automatically given positions as soldiers because of their experience. The women had to 'earn’ it. The general was much healthier back then and he decided that to join the army the women had to prove they could take him on one on one. No one succeeded, of course. Those who gave up then were given hard labor as slaves to the farms. Those like me who tried the challenge… Their masculine pride was punished with a reminder of their status as women. A brothel, to be more specific. Your mother saw more in me, so she saved me from that. I’m not sure what happened to the others." She continues her casual reminiscing.

Nash gapes at her. "What...? That's. No. I mean, he can't have. How was that accepted, as a.. I mean, 'masculine pride'? F-for wanting to be human? For wanting to fight and die for their country? That's a-a normal fuckin' aspiration, that's." His face twists. "Ngh.. I.. that system of dominance over women, is, it's barbaric. I mean." He gestures rapidly. "Our *goddess* is a woman. W-we prostrate ourselves before her, as we are right to. How could the, the feminine essence be ensnared and degraded in this way?"

She seems confused. "Well… You wouldn’t have a brothel full of men, would you? It’s uniquely feminine labour. So it’s worshipping women in its own way to visit them. And we don’t have a *singular* goddess, Libra is just one of the gods in her pantheon. But yes, people idolize women. That’s what it means to appreciate uniquely feminine jobs for how they help. You support women by considering what I do a motherhood role. I’m honoured by that. That’s life, Nash."

"W-well..." He bites his nail, thinking. "I suppose there's something to that? The idea that it's a form of worship. But, I mean, wouldn't it be degrading...? Wouldn't it be exploitation? Because, like, the women aren't necessarily dictating, the, the interactions. And it's framed as a punishment. So like..." He struggles for words.
"You’ll understand someday, Nash. You should get going. Kori needs to rest."

*Idiot. You're just proving to her that you don't understand women or their needs, or how they function in this world. Do you haaaaate women, Nash? Do you hate the idea that they could wield power in a dynamic? Fucking piece of shit.*
"Right." He says hollowly. "Yes, I'll try to understand. I'll keep trying. I want to support you. However I can."
*I respect women.*
He nods. "I'll see you later."
"See you later, Nash."
Nash returns to the room he was previously in.
Orion is there. Ruth is still unconscious. "Hey, Nash… Was everything fine?"
He clears his throat. "Yes. Everything was fine."
"The uh… Captain still hasn’t woken up." He scratches his head awkwardly.
Nash rolls his eyes. "Just slap her around a bit, she'll come to."
Nash kicks her in the side.
"Wait-" He stops Nash. "Aren’t you uh… Scared she’ll hit us again? Remember this morning?"
Nash frowns. "She'll hit us again no matter what we do."
"Yeah, but she can’t if she’s asleep… As long as we don’t wake her up… We’re in control."
"What are you suggesting, then?"
"…" He looks down at her nervously. "Do you want to like… Get revenge, or something? There’s no telling when she’ll get knocked out again. And she owes us for being a total bitch."
Nash's face twists. "You.. what kind of revenge are you thinking about, then?" He spreads his hands exaggeratedly. "Floor's all yours."
"I don't know! We can't hurt her or she might wake up. We could like... Uh... Any ideas?" He looks back at Nash expectantly.
"I don't fuckin' know! What's the point, if not hurting her? Drawing on her face in marker? Please." He laughs bitterly.

"We could like... Hurt her indirectly. Like that womanhood purity monks have. Uh, I mean- Like not all the way. She'd outright kill us if it woke her up. But I mean like... She at least owes us a kiss or something, right? For putting up with her all this time."

Nash blinks. His throat is dry. "Nnnh... you.. I...?" He makes a confused noise. "D-does she? I mean, we're, w-we're uh, kind of pains in the asses too." *Stop stuttering. You sound like such a fucking pussy. Don't you want to protect women? Isn't this the opposite of everything you've claimed to be advocating for? B-but, at the same time, you just. You're supposed to..? Isn't that right..? This is the sort of conflict you're intended to be feeling, right? The desire to help women, to understand their problems, w-with the natural male urge. Right? It's a natural instinct. An impulse. Every man, somewhere deep in his heart, just wants... for them to stop talking. To make them stop talking. Using your mouth, or whatever. Aaaaaaaaaah! You're sick! You're sick in the head!*

*You sound like suuuuch a fucking pussy! You heard mom! She's the one with all the power here, not you! Brandishing it like a weapon! Smacking you around like it's her prerogative! Even this is an extension of that! She's, like, drawing us in! With her feminine, uh... her.. fuck! Look at Orion. He had no problem suggesting this. He wants to go through with it! Stop being such a coward dickless eunuch limp-wristed pansy!! You know who you are! You know exactly who you are!*
"Y-yeah." Nash says. *Stop fucking stuttering!* "She does owe us. Both of us. For our respect. We've offered so much of it, right?" *Stop looking to him for approval.*
"Yeah, exactly!" He goes a bit quieter, cautiously avoiding waking her up. "So uh... She hits you more. I think you've earned first dibs on her."
"Right." He coughs. "I guess I'll.. just go for it?" A question.
*God, I'm so fucking scared.*
"Yeah. Let me know how it feels, I guess." He steps back a bit for Nash to have full control of the unmoving body.
Nash sinks to his knees, putting himself on equal level with her. He cautiously touches her wrist, testing the waters.
No reaction. The rhythmic rising of her chest up and down is the only thing distinguishing her from a corpse right now.

She's soft. She's scarred, of course, from battle - but there's an inherent gentle quality to her skin that Nash hasn't ever felt before in anyone other than Mother. Who he shouldn't... be thinking about, right now, huh?
This is a.. romantic, interaction? That he's about to have. With a woman. That's something of note. *I'm so scared. I'm so... I'm so scared. Somebody help me.*
She's soft. That's an attractive quality. She's attractive, right?!? He thinks she's attractive, right?!?
Nash places his hand on her cheek. Also soft.
He leans forwards.
Her lips are soft, too. They don't taste like anything.

He draws back. After a year. After a century. He feels vaguely like he's been swallowed whole, something about the fabric of his body pulled taut, pinned like a butterfly to a corkboard. He's peeled apart. Something raw and twitching is exposed. The fear has not left him.
"How was it?"
*I should say it was good, right? It's supposed to be good. It's supposed to be fulfilling! Get your shit together!*
He shrugs, performing ironic detachment. "It was fine. She's no generational talent at this."
"Yeah, figures." He chuckles awkwardly. "I mean she'd have found a guy to stay with if she was good, right?" He approaches her.
Nash doesn't say anything.
"You good, Nash?" He kneels down next to Ruth. He picks up Ruth's hand and give it a sarcastic kiss of 'respect'.
"Y-yeah. I'm fine. Better than fine!!!" He laughs sardonically. "I'm greeeeat. I feel great about doing this."
*Fuck, that might have come across as sarcastic. That wasn't. The goal.*
"We deserve this, so it's fine."

"Exactly. She might as well be grateful." He casually drops Ruth's hand onto the ground and goes to kiss her lips. His mouth forces hers open with dispassionate arrogance. 

The impact of Ruth's hand hitting the ground causes her to stir slightly as she slowly opens her eyes.
*Oh shit, oh shit, oh shit, oh shit.*

Orion backs away in a panic. "Shit!"

Ruth slowly sits up, looking around. "Where is Washington Hamill?"
